metadata.name: THE YELLOW GEM
metadata.description:
Story behind the artwork:

My personal interpretation of Norway. Painterly mountain landscape. Layers upon layers. Creating depth while keeping it as dreamy and painting-like as I have in my mind.

What stands out are the striking yellow houses, which for me have something magical about them. It seems as if they were color-coordinated with the scenery. Color harmony at its finest. 

The first collector gets the Original uncompressed TIFF and Original JPG files on request.

Edition 1/1
3293 x 4117 px / 300dpi
Artist: Kathrin Federer
